# Simple terms (user vocabulary)

The user speaks in **simple terms** defined in [`docs/agent/SIMPLE_TERMS.md`](docs/agent/SIMPLE_TERMS.md). **Always** treat that file as the canonical user ↔ agent dictionary for diagram/canvas/splice conversation.

## Before acting on diagram feedback

1. Read `docs/agent/SIMPLE_TERMS.md` when the user names canvas parts, routing, bends, bundles, or stack order.
2. Map every simple term to official/code names before editing layout, routing, or nodes.
3. Reply using the user's simple words when discussing UI; use official names in code/comments only when needed.

## One-line model (memorize)

**Cable → buffer tube → fan-out → labels → handle → left leg → fusion splice dot → right leg → handle → labels → fan-out → buffer tube → cable**

## Key mappings (do not guess)

| User says | Means |
|-----------|--------|
| **Corner** | 90° bend on **left leg** or **right leg** |
| **Bend budget** | **2 corners total** per splice (left + right combined) — **EDGE-004** |
| **Tube bundle** / **shared run** | Same buffer tube → same target cable; **bundle trunk** / **jogX** |
| **Center nest** | Staggered corners in a bundle; **EDGE-005**, **EDGE-007** |
| **Fiber order** | Top→bottom inside one tube — **FBR-001** |
| **Tube order** | Top→bottom of tubes on cable — **TUB-006** |
| **Row order** | Top→bottom splice rows on diagram — **ROW-***, **DOM-*** |

Fan-out curves on the **cable** are **not** splice corners.

Expanded part names: [`docs/agent/CANVAS_GLOSSARY.md`](docs/agent/CANVAS_GLOSSARY.md). Rule IDs: [`docs/agent/RULE_DICTIONARY.md`](docs/agent/RULE_DICTIONARY.md).
